          text: 'The primary driver of GEO market growth is the shift of informational query volume from traditional search engines to AI-generated answer platforms. Secondary drivers include increasing brand awareness of AI citation risk (brands discovering they are misrepresented or absent from AI answers), the proliferation of AI-native interfaces in consumer and enterprise software, and the growing recognition that traditional SEO skills do not transfer directly to AI citation optimisation. These structural drivers are independent of any single platform and compound as AI search becomes more deeply embedded in how people find information.'
        }
