        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'How should organisations assess the ROI of GEO investment?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'GEO ROI is best assessed through the lens of brand visibility risk rather than direct revenue attribution, at least in the early stages. The relevant question is not "how much revenue did this citation generate?" but "what is the cost of being absent or misrepresented when a potential customer asks an AI engine about our category?" As GEO measurement tools mature, attribution models that link AI citation presence to pipeline and revenue are becoming possible, but the more immediately defensible case is the risk-mitigation framing: organisations that establish citation presence early face lower remediation costs than those who address it reactively.'
        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'Will GEO replace SEO?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'GEO will not replace SEO in the near term; the two disciplines will coexist as AI search and traditional search coexist. The more accurate framing is that GEO will grow as a proportion of total search marketing investment as AI search handles a larger share of queries. Organisations that invest in GEO alongside SEO, rather than instead of it, are positioned to maintain visibility across both channels as the balance shifts.'
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://geooptimised.com/' },
